ltiple\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"nightmare_sng_1\" cefr=\"b2\" ox3000=\"y\" hclass=\"sense\" sensenum=\"1\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><div class=\"symbols\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"symbols\"><a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxford3000-5000?dataset=english&amp;list=ox3000&amp;level=b2\"><span class=\"ox3ksym_b2\">&nbsp;</span></a></div></span> <span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">a dream that is very frightening or unpleasant</span><ul class=\"examples\" hclass=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">He still has nightmares about the accident.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She has a recurring nightmare about being stuck in a lift.</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"extra_examples\" id=\"nightmare_unbox_1\"><span class=\"box_title\">Extra Examples</span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Survivors suffer flashbacks, nightmares and severe depression.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The faces of all the people he had killed haunted his nightmares.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">The film gave me nightmares.</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"unx\">Horror films always give me nightmares.</span></li></ul></span></div><div class=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"collapse\"><span class=\"unbox\" unbox=\"snippet\" id=\"nightmare_unbox_2\"><span class=\"box_title\">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"unbox\">adjective</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">awful</li><li class=\"li\">horrible</li><li class=\"li\">terrible</li><li class=\"li\">…</li></ul><span class=\"unbox\">verb + nightmare</span><ul class=\"collocs_list\"><li class=\"li\">have</li><li class=\"li\">suffer</li><